 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-tska","title":"Opt 4.3: Placeholder String Reuse","description":"# Optimization 4.3: Placeholder String Reuse

## Summary
Common placeholder strings like "[image]", "[file]", "[code]" are allocated
repeatedly. Using static strings or Cow reduces allocations in hot paths.

## Location
- **File:** Various connector parsing (src/connectors/*.rs)
- **Related:** Message processing, content extraction

## Current State
\`\`\`rust
// Each call allocates a new String
fn process_content(content: &str) -> String {
    if is_image(content) {
        return String::from("[image]");  // Allocates ~16 bytes
    }
    if is_file(content) {
        return String::from("[file]");
    }
    content.to_string()
}
\`\`\`

## Problem Analysis
1. **Repeated allocations:** Same placeholder created thousands of times
2. **Short-lived strings:** Allocated, used once, dropped
3. **Memory fragmentation:** Many small allocations
4. **Cache pollution:** Allocator metadata for tiny strings

## Proposed Solution

### Option A: Static &str Constants (Simplest)
\`\`\`rust
/// Common placeholder strings
pub mod placeholders {
    pub const IMAGE: &str = "[image]";
    pub const FILE: &str = "[file]";
    pub const CODE: &str = "[code]";
    pub const BINARY: &str = "[binary]";
    pub const TRUNCATED: &str = "[truncated]";
    pub const AUDIO: &str = "[audio]";
    pub const VIDEO: &str = "[video]";
    pub const PDF: &str = "[pdf]";
}

// Use Cow for mixed return types
use std::borrow::Cow;

fn process_content(content: &str) -> Cow<'static, str> {
    if is_image(content) {
        return Cow::Borrowed(placeholders::IMAGE);  // Zero allocation
    }
    if is_file(content) {
        return Cow::Borrowed(placeholders::FILE);
    }
    Cow::Owned(content.to_string())  // Only allocates when needed
}
\`\`\`

### Option B: Interned Strings with Arc (for complex placeholders)
\`\`\`rust
use std::sync::Arc;
use once_cell::sync::Lazy;

/// Dynamic placeholders that include runtime data
pub static PLACEHOLDER_TRUNCATED_KB: Lazy<Arc<str>> = 
    Lazy::new(|| Arc::from(format!("[truncated: >{}KB]", MAX_CONTENT_KB)));

pub static PLACEHOLDER_ERROR: Lazy<Arc<str>> =
    Lazy::new(|| Arc::from("[error: could not process content]"));
\`\`\`

### Option C: Centralized Placeholder Registry
\`\`\`rust
use std::collections::HashMap;
use once_cell::sync::Lazy;
use std::sync::Arc;

/// Registry of all placeholder strings
pub struct PlaceholderRegistry {
    static_placeholders: HashMap<&'static str, &'static str>,
    dynamic_placeholders: HashMap<String, Arc<str>>,
}

impl PlaceholderRegistry {
    pub fn get(&self, key: &str) -> Option<&str> {
        self.static_placeholders.get(key).copied()
    }

    pub fn get_dynamic(&self, key: &str) -> Option<Arc<str>> {
        self.dynamic_placeholders.get(key).cloned()
    }
}

pub static PLACEHOLDERS: Lazy<PlaceholderRegistry> = Lazy::new(|| {
    let mut reg = PlaceholderRegistry {
        static_placeholders: HashMap::new(),
        dynamic_placeholders: HashMap::new(),
    };

    reg.static_placeholders.insert("image", "[image]");
    reg.static_placeholders.insert("file", "[file]");
    // ...

    reg
});
\`\`\`

